<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="36080764-e82e-59d5-861e-e10289cba326" activityNameId="925700b2-f67f-4133-a9a9-6de22cb3eeda" parentActivityId="ebbf9dbd-222f-47eb-b080-18f0677182a9" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">cement production, CEM II/A</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">CEM II/A</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Portland composite cement</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the clinker in the silo to be used for cement production and with the additional ingredients of the cement at the gate of the cement plant. The dataset includes energy use, input of grinding aids and input of infrastructure.
 </includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the cement produced in the cement mill. The dataset does not include particulate emission, packaging and administration.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The dataset describes the production of cement (CEM II/A) in Switzerland and covers the representative production mix of CEM II/A-D, CEM II/A-LL, CEM II/A-M(D-LL), CEM II/A-M(V-LL) and CEM II/A-S according to SN EN 197-1.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">In Switzerland, according to the Swiss standard SN EN 197-1:2011, cement CEM II, also known as Portland composite cement, has 65-94% of clinker and is mixed with different materials, such as limestone, ground granulated blast furnace slag, fly ash, pozzolan, burnt shale, silica fume, among others.</text>
        </generalComment>
        <tag>combined production</tag>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="36cd730c-4485-4fe9-8efe-8850f771796d">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2394:Manufacture of cement, lime and plaster</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="131278d6-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">CH</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents production of cement CEM II/A for Switzerland.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">In this dataset, the production of CEM II/A is described, where clinker (77.7%) is ground together with gypsum (4.9%) and mixed with limestone (15%), silica fume, blast furnace slag and ground granulated blast furnace slag (GGBFS). The activity includes also the input of electricity used for the grinding of the clinker, grinding aids (ethylene glycol and iron sulfate) and heat (heavy fuel oil) for the drying of additions.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2017-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="false">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Time period corresponds to data collection (2017-2021).</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
